			<h2>
				Amy Perrin Ross
            </h2>
            <p>            
                APN, MSN, CNRN, MSCN
                <br />
                MS NEED Steering Committee and Syllabus Committee
            </p>
            <br />

		    <p>
                Amy Perrin Ross is a board-certified Neuroscience Nurse and is the Neuroscience Program 
                Coordinator at Loyola University Medical Center in Maywood, Illinois, U.S.A. She obtained 
                her Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree from Loyola University School of Nursing, Chicago, 
                Illinois, and a Master of Science in Nursing from the Graduate School of Nursing of Loyola 
                University, U.S.A.
            </p>
            <p>
                Amy is an advanced practice multiple sclerosis (MS) nurse who coordinates the MS clinic at 
                Loyola University Medical Center in Maywood Illinois. In her role she has coordinated multiple 
                clinical research trials in MS. She is a Member of the Consortium of Multiple Sclerosis Centers 
                and the Multiple Sclerosis Nursing International Certification Board. Amy is the President of 
                the International Organization of Multiple Sclerosis Nurses (IOMSN). She has authored numerous 
                articles and book chapters on MS and dementia.
            </p>
            <p>
                In addition, Amy is a Clinical Nurse Consultant with the National Multiple Sclerosis Society (NMSS), 
                a Member of the Health Care Advisory Council for the Multiple Sclerosis Association of America and 
                a former Board Member of the Consortium of Multiple Sclerosis Centers. She has been an invited speaker 
                at numerous meetings and conferences and has been very active in neuroscience clinical research for 
                over 20 years.
            </p>
            <p>
                Amy is also certified by the American Board of Neuroscience Nurses and by the Multiple Sclerosis 
                Nursing International Certification Board.
            </p>
